My favorite card game is garbage which can be played with 2+ people.

You deal 10 cards to each player and set it up face down in a row or two if want to take up less space. The remaining deck is placed in the middle.

The object of the game is to be the first player to line up your cards in a sequence starting with the ace.
The player left of the dealer goes first by drawing the top card from the deck. In the first round each player has 10 cards. The cards are numbered 1 to 10 starting from the left. When a numbered card is drawn, the card is placed in the corresponding spot.

For example, a 5 drawn will be put face up in the fifth spot on your row. The face down card in that spot is flipped up and placed accordingly in your row and so on. When the player can no longer make a move, discard the current card. The next player to the left can choose to take the top discard, or draw the top card of the deck. The kings are wildcards and can be put in any spot. The jacks and queens are garbage and are discarded when picked up. Aces are used for the 1 spot.

Once a player has flipped up all his/her cards, each other player gets 1 more turn. All the players that were able to flip up all 10 cards will only be dealt 9 cards in the next round, and will only need to get a sequence of 1 to 9. Players that did not flip up all the cards will have to play the next round with 10 cards again and you keep going until someone gets down to zero.

Bingo - each player gets 5 cards each which are dealt face down so only they can see them. Place the rest of the cards in a pile and pick up the first number, if you have that card you place it down. If you already have more than one card with the same number when the cards are dealt they can be put down straight away, the winner is the first person to place all their cards down
